title: 820-2533, no 5V_S3 .
message: Yes, 3V3_S5 is missing. Measured on pin 1 R4212. I do have G2_EN (pn 13), but only .722V on 3V3_S5 ENTRIP (pn 6). So I wont get 3v3_S5.

title: 820-2533, no 5V_S3 .
message: .7V on ENTRIP is what it is supposed to be. If there is no short on 3v3_s5 it look like a dead U7200.

title: 820-2533, no 5V_S3 .
message:
Hey Duke.
Noticed pin 20 on U7100 was a bit burnt. So I replaced it, along with C7196, C7126 and R7120.  I would have replaced the FETS but I do not have a donor for this. Is there another board that uses these I can pull themm from?  I also replaced U7200 for the second time.

I Now have 3v3_s5. Also have 1 fan spin when I press power button. 
While the fan spins I briefly get PM_SLP_S3 and PM_SLP_S4 at 3.3V. Im still not getting PP5V_S3. Here is a vid of what happens on PP5V_S3 when I press the power button. 

---------> [url]https://photos.app.goo.gl/Y30RVWbDHSRrT85C2[/url]

Thanks Duke. Have a good one.

title: 820-2533, no 5V_S3 .
message: u7100 had burnt pin (20). I replaced it. Both sides of L7101 and L7100 start at 72 Ohms and drop very slowly. I held it for 3 or 4 mins to about 60Ohms then took probes off. I think it would have continued to drop. So maybe a small short? I dont have a donor for this... Do you know of any other boards with compatible FETS?

title: 820-2533, no 5V_S3 .
message: The usual culprits R7112/20/21 checked and the traces? This will probably be an issue in the Vcore area.
